definition: male/staminate/grand/imposing/powerful/mighty/person or state having great power and influence

sentences.english: I don't care how big. I just want a buck.
sentences.chinese: 我不在乎它有多大，我只是想要一隻雄鹿。

sentences.english: He's seen a pair of antlers, he's turning into a stag.
sentences.chinese: 從倒影中他看到一對鹿角，他已經變成一頭雄鹿了。

sentences.english: With the aid of the Hunter, the Horse soon overcame the Stag.
sentences.chinese: 隨著援助的獵人，馬很快戰勝了雄鹿。

sentences.english: Bucks Pistons with the other hand, lost three, including two lost to the Pistons .
sentences.chinese: 雄鹿跟活塞相反，連輸三場，其中兩次敗給活塞。

sentences.english: So far the stalemate between the Bucks and the Yi camp continues.
sentences.chinese: 眼下，雄鹿隊和易之隊之間的僵局還在繼續。

sentences.english: "He's done a great job, " said Bucks center Andrew Bogut.
sentences.chinese: “乾得很漂亮，”雄鹿中鋒博古特說。

sentences.english: Williams, the starter at the point, is also a free agent.

sentences.english: NBA and has had a very successful season with the Milwaukee Bucks.

sentences.english: Yi's signing is a happy ending for all parties.
sentences.chinese: 阿聯和雄鹿簽約，是一個皆大歡喜結局。

sentences.english: I was extremely pleased that I shot at the stag with cherry stones two years earlier.
sentences.chinese: 我非常開心兩年前我用櫻桃核擊中了這隻雄鹿。

sentences.english: I think the coaching staff will make the adjustments.
sentences.chinese: 我認爲雄鹿的教練組會做出調整的。

sentences.english: Stag have large branch-like horns which are called antlers.
sentences.chinese: 雄鹿有被稱爲多叉鹿角的，像大樹枝般的角。

sentences.english: A pack of wolves nearly tired down a buck.
sentences.chinese: 一羣狼把一頭雄鹿趕得幾乎跑不動了。

sentences.english: A spike a young buck walks into a clearing near the feeder.
sentences.chinese: 一隻年輕的雄鹿走進了餵食區。

sentences.english: Want to Rake in Big Bucks in Your Business?
sentences.chinese: 要耙大雄鹿在您的企業？

sentences.english: This is still called the "Stag Night".
sentences.chinese: 這一天如今仍被稱爲“雄鹿之夜”。
